replies.bodyText:
In Rest.li world, when you have a PathSpecSet you may have logic that is skipped if the projection doesn't include a specific field:
if (pathSpecSet.contains(MyRecord.fields().subrecord()) {
    // do a bunch of stuff that is costly but unnecessary if the field subrecord isn't requested
}

And then given the ResourceContext, you can easily build a PathSpecSet with PathSpecSet.of(resourceContext.getProjectionMask()).
When no projection is specified, the ProjectionMask is null and you want to make sure that contains(PathSpec) returns true for any PathSpec and that's the meaning of a fullProjection.
